# Wipe file from git history (filter-repo)

if not already installed:

````bash
pip install git-filter-repo


backup repo (or use a fresh clone in a different directory)

```bash
git branch backup-before-filter
````

Remove the file from all history:

```bash
git filter-repo --path {relative-path-to-file} --invert-paths
```

if that fails, try

```bash
python -m git_filter_repo --path {relative-path-to-file} --invert-paths
```

you'll have to add remote origin again.

```bash
git remote add origin {remote-url}
```

Then push the rewritten history to the intended remote:

```bash
git push --force origin {branch-name}
```
